eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 10 Years
Maximum age: 99 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.

Female participants must have a negative pregnancy test within 7 days of entering into the study; both men and women of child bearing potential must agree to use adequate methods of contraception for the duration of the treatment; women must avoid pregnancy, and men must avoid fathering children while in the study and for 6 months following the last study drug treatment
Active serious systemic disease, including active bacterial or fungal infection.

Eligible tumor and premalignant lesion sites include oral cavity (buccal mucosal, gingival, floor of mouth, dorsal/ventral tongue, pharyngeal wall), oropharynx, larynx (glottis, supraglottis, subglottis, epiglottis), hypopharynx paranasal sinus and nasal cavity
Patients with known involvement of the CNS by malignancy will be excluded.

Visceral metastases (including cerebral metastases) from castration-resistant prostate cancer (CRPC) (> 2 lung and/or liver metastases [size >= 2 cm]; lymphadenopathy exceeding 6 cm in short-axis diameter or any size pelvic lymphadenopathy if it is thought to be a contributor to concurrent hydronephrosis), as assessed by computed tomography (CT), magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) or chest X-ray within the 8 weeks prior to registration
Liver disease such as cirrhosis or severe hepatic impairment (Childs-Pugh class C)
Paraffin-embedded tumor tissue blocks of patients enrolled in North Central Cancer Treatment Group (NCCTG) 86-72-51 or 93-72-02 and who had the diagnosis of low-grade glioma
Any medical or psychiatric illness which in the opinion of the principal investigator would compromise the patients ability to tolerate this treatment

groups.description: Pediatric patients were assigned to Dotarem group only.
groups.name: Dotarem 2 (gadoterate meglumine )

outcome_measures.measure: Incidence second of primary lung tumors

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Induction: pre-infusion (0 hr), 0.5 hr post-infusion on Day 1 of Cycle 1; Cycle 1 Days 8, 15; pre-infusion (within 5 hr prior to dose), 0.5 hr post-infusion on Day 1 on Cycles 2, 4; pre-infusion (within 5 hr prior to dose) on Day 1 of Cycle 6 (infusion duration: 90 minutes) (1 cycle: 21 days)
outcome_measures.measure: Observed Plasma Concentration of Polatuzumab Vedotin Unconjugated MMAE
outcome_measures.time_frame: Pre-infusion (0 hr) on Day 1 of Cycle 1 up to pre-infusion (within 5 hr prior to dose) on Day 1 of Cycle 6. Detailed timeframe is given in outcome measure description.

outcome_measures.analysis_method: All observed adverse events will be summarized in terms of type (organ affected or laboratory determination), severity (by the CTCAE v4.0), time of onset (i.e. day/week from start of treatment), attribution and reversibility or outcome. Tables will be created to summarize these toxicities and side effects, overall, by dose level, and by course.
outcome_measures.measure: Incidence of toxicity, defined as adverse events considered to be at least possibly drug-related
